 231:Core/Src/port.c **** 
 232:Core/Src/port.c ****     /* A function that implements a task must not exit or attempt to return to
 233:Core/Src/port.c ****      * its caller as there is nothing to return to.  If a task wants to exit it
 234:Core/Src/port.c ****      * should instead call vTaskDelete( NULL ).
 235:Core/Src/port.c ****      *
 236:Core/Src/port.c ****      * Artificially force an assert() to be triggered if configASSERT() is
 237:Core/Src/port.c ****      * defined, then stop here so application writers can catch the error. */
 238:Core/Src/port.c ****     configASSERT( uxCriticalNesting == ~0UL );
