 383:Core/Src/port.c ****         {
 384:Core/Src/port.c ****             /* When the hardware implements 8 priority bits, there is no way for
 385:Core/Src/port.c ****              * the software to configure PRIGROUP to not have sub-priorities. As
 386:Core/Src/port.c ****              * a result, the least significant bit is always used for sub-priority
 387:Core/Src/port.c ****              * and there are 128 preemption priorities and 2 sub-priorities.
 388:Core/Src/port.c ****              *
 389:Core/Src/port.c ****              * This may cause some confusion in some cases - for example, if
 390:Core/Src/port.c ****              * configMAX_SYSCALL_INTERRUPT_PRIORITY is set to 5, both 5 and 4
 391:Core/Src/port.c ****              * priority interrupts will be masked in Critical Sections as those
